				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Agreed Samxp and the thing is we can't, and we all know it, and that is a problem that needs to be fixed. Saying what you can solo is one thing, to say what you can solo for meaningful experience is something totally different. A necro solo's things for meaningful experience consistantly that a mage will post and say I was able to solo a mob in that same zone, but it is not worthwhile to do. I see that as a huge problem, I see from other posts I am not alone in that thought. I hope all that agree post so SoE gets the point and fixes this BALLANCE ISSUE. yes it is a ballance issue if other int classes can consistantly solo mobs for meaningful experience that we are barely able to do, and at a ton more risk. However it isn't even that close, the mobs we can barely solo are blue, as they take yellows and reds consistanly. See a problem yet SoE? 
<br />

<br />
To the people who play a magician class ballance does mean in all 3 areas. Grouping, raiding, and YES SOLOING. Soloing is not a bad word, it was part of our class for 60 levels of play. One expansion should not change that, it did. The slaughter light blues yields shit for experience, and we all know it. STOP giving aid and support to SoE by saynig it is ok to lose what we once enjoyed. It is not something many of us want to give up. You may, and that is fine, though you should also agree soloing should always be a magician option as it is for a chanter/necro and wizard. Why 3 of the 4 int based classes, when a mage was always a soloable class. SoE you listening? Return what we lost in this arena, as you helped necro's gain in their weak area's, grouping and raiding, druids in their healing skills, paladins in their ability to get and keep aggro as well as a very well rounded class. Don't stop with the mage class.
<br />

<br />
Calebe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
