				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Little clue, I play all classes with exception of paladin, half a dozen are 60+, the rest are 55+, so I have at least a teeny amount of experience with these classes.  I also read most class boards, and when I do decide to post, I don't exactly sign each one with that particular class character name, and have yet to have anyone act as juvenile as this board when it comes to screaming "Board troll" simply because my main is not of that particular class.  Also, it wasn't a drivby, it was simply pointing out that the last half dozen of you for the past week have been squabbling over the same drawn out issues amonst yourselves with not a single mind changed in your rantings.  I simply assumed someone needed to hand you a clue that your post had been beaten to death as none of the posters (Samxp, Cal, rank, etc...) seemed to be smart enough to figure that out.
<br />

<br />
Also, Rank, though I appreciate you trying flame me with a semi-intelligent comeback, I suggest you understand the meaning of the descriptive words you use in order to flame someone without making yourself look stupid in the proccess.
<br />

<br />
Ebonics:  a nonstandard variety of English spoken by some American blacks -- called also Black English vernacular 
<br />

<br />
My use of standard proper english seems a bit over your head, I apologize and will try to stick to 2 syllable words from now on.
