On the subject of DC pets, I personally don't want one. At all, period, none, nope, don't want to even think about it more. Now your probably wondering why I am so set on not wanting it. The reason is very simple, they take XP from the group or me if I'm solo, and depending on the amount of damage it does versus the group/you. I don't know if you all remember the good old days when pet use to take 50% of your xp if you didn't do more then 50% of the damage (talk about LONG med times cause of all of the over nuking). With A DC pet I would have to spend even MORE mana to get up over that curve to make sure i got the xp versus the pet, which would mean even longer med times. To me this doesn't sound like a solution. Granted the other option would be to not nuke so hard and get low end xp (humm a lot like killing light blues). There are other down sides with a DC pet, I can't suspend the pet so I can move elsewhere in the zone, which means I would need to pacify/harmony all of the mobs from where DC pet is (begining of zone) to where xp group is usually not at the entrance of a zone <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> There are only a few DC mobs in any given zone (something like 3). Ohh and summoned mobs period in the game are really lacking for some of the lower tiers. Also the fact a DC mob could become not my soul trusted pet makes me nervous (yea I got charm but doesn't mean I use it alot or even really think we should have it, but thats a different subject/topic). And so that you know I'm not a weird case, yes I do group with friends that are capabile of having DC pets, but as pointed out that is not always an option. The group can be killer when you get one as long as the group is way outdamaging the pet(s).
<br />

<br />
I do agree that we need some balancing for our class, and well that same statement can be made about a lot of classes also. I just really hope that we don't get DC. (IMHO)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
