			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually if you look back at the beginning of the post, I actually was trying to convey the issues dealing with the post topic, which is DC pet vs. mage pet.  Suddenly I recieved a lot of feedback from individuals who weren't even replying to anything I had said remotely having to do with the post topic.  These people are who I classified as whiners, if you weren't one of them, you should have taken no offense to my posting.  As more people decided to jump on the bandwagon, I am sure I got a bit more rude about it, not intended but it is human reaction.
<br />

<br />
I am not in any way worried about mage vs. bst soloing, and this had nothing to do with the current post topic.  There is however another post dealing with this so I suggest you take your comments there on that topic.  I did however state many valid facts as to why there is such a difference in DC'd mobs vs. mage pets(and all summoned pets for that matter) but again recieved many replies claiming I was somehow against mage improvement simply because I disagreed with others comments made.  Most of the people replying had no personal knowledge of DC ad charmed mobs issues of aggro, exp taken, difference in NPC power vs summoned pet stats, and were simply making generalizations based on something they 'saw the other day'.  I apologize if making first hand knowledge become clear suddenly made me seem offensive for giving you the facts.
<br />

<br />
I just grow weary of enjoying my mage so much, and while I am all for class improvement, it seems that many mages don't know exactly what improvements they want other than essentially other classes utility.  Most mages want slow, root, snare, and of course a more powerful pet, but don't seem to realize that unfortunatly, the class will never recieve ALL of those abilities.  Make a clear request for one or two of those things and what exactly you feel would make the magician pet powerful enough to become an efficient counterpart.  I am thinking from the devs standpoint on class balancing, not some immature feud between mages and bsts.  What exactly needs to be done to the mage pet to give them the ability to tank sufficiently against the mobs you intend for them to tank, and be rational about the requests, as the more power you intend to give to the pet, the less likely you will be to ever be considered for class utilities such as slows, mana regen, nuking power, root/snare etc.  
<br />

<br />
I have never been against magician upgrades, no matter the flames I have recieved nor given, I simply debate the issues that people insist they MUST have to be effective because they can't consider total balance of their class that hasn't achieved flagging to some of those upper tiers that the pet becomes mush in 10 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Venerable Longfanz Beaztmaster Feral Lord</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
